cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CE 

The paper focuses on vehicular cloud computing, which is a subfield of computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also deals with optimization problems and algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions constraints and limited resources, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
